Fitting in R

Packages

library(vcdExtra)
library(fitdistrplus)
library(haven) ## read sas file

Generate variable from Poisson distribution

set.seed(123)
x <- rpois(10000,10)
barplot(table(x))

Fitting distributions using vcdExtra

Verify whether given variable follows binomial, negative binomial or poisson distribution

m1 <- goodfit(x, "binomial")
size was not given, taken as maximum count
m2 <- goodfit(x, "nbinomial")
m3 <- goodfit(x, "poisson")
summary(m1)

     Goodness-of-fit test for binomial distribution

                      X^2 df P(> X^2)
Likelihood Ratio 2210.381 22        0
summary(m2)

     Goodness-of-fit test for nbinomial distribution

                      X^2 df   P(> X^2)
Likelihood Ratio 29.73244 21 0.09749794
summary(m3)

     Goodness-of-fit test for poisson distribution

Practical example from real data

Lets focus on variable informing how many children under 14 years are in households (variable LOS_LT14)

barplot(table(bbgd$LOS_LT14))

What kind of distribution it is?

Is it poisson?

dist_po <- goodfit(bbgd$LOS_LT14, "poisson")
plot(dist_po)

summary(dist_po)

     Goodness-of-fit test for poisson distribution

                      X^2 df P(> X^2)
Likelihood Ratio 3833.142  8        0

Is it negative binomial?

dis_nb <- goodfit(bbgd$LOS_LT14, "nbinom")
NaNs producedNaNs producedNaNs producedNaNs producedNaNs producedNaNs producedNaNs produced
summary(dis_nb)

     Goodness-of-fit test for nbinomial distribution

                      X^2 df      P(> X^2)
Likelihood Ratio 633.1599  7 1.754422e-132
plot(dis_nb)

dis_nb <- goodfit(bbgd$LOS_LT14, "binom")
size was not given, taken as maximum count
summary(dis_nb)

     Goodness-of-fit test for binomial distribution

                      X^2 df P(> X^2)
Likelihood Ratio 5002.667  8        0
